<title>SRI LANKA: Ceylon Brewery up 1.9 pct at 35 rupees.</title>
<headline>Ceylon Brewery up 1.9 pct at 35 rupees.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-01-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ceylon Brewery Ltd rose 1.9 percent, or one rupee, to 35, as retail investors bought 7,000 shares on Monday, brokers said.</p>
<p>&quot;The company is doing very well since late 1995 when the government slashed excise duty by over 70 percent,&quot; said a broker dealing with retail investors.</p>
<p>Demand for the company's beers had risen sharply after the price reduction, the broker said.</p>
<p>-- Colombo newsroom (941) 434319</p>
